This paper discusses citation impact indicators in scientific journals, which is a topic that falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as they both deal with the organization and retrieval of scientific literature. The sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possibility, as it involves the evaluation of research impact in the field of security. The sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible, as they both involve the analysis of large datasets and the evaluation of research impact.
